The reinforced ultrasonic waves are active in the TRP-4 ion channels, which are found in the membranes of some worm cells.
With the sound waves, these channels open and activate the cells they are linked to, a report from the journal Nature Communications.
In order to control the nematodes using ultrasound waves, Chalasani genetically modified the worms so that some of their motor neurons contain the TRP-4 ion channels.
