Xi calls for the opening of the economy to the wider world
It is necessary to open up the economy to the wider world to boost growth, President Xi Jinping told the group, whose task is to reform the governance on Tuesday.
"China should be involved in attracting foreign investment and expertise and improving open policies," the central group's head of the Deepening of the Over-Chief Reforms said regarding the 16th meeting.
Promoting opening up in the in-reliferation will give new impetus and vitality, and will also provide new room for economic growth, says Xi.
The lead group adopted a number of directives, including a negative list of market regulatory access, the loosening of border control policy, support for state-owned enterprises (SOEs) to absorb private capital and reorganise the SGI system.
The statement states that a negative list will be drawn up to identify sectors and enterprises that are outside the investment limits.
This system will be gradually tested and improved through test programmes.
This step is significant because it will provide a greater role for the market in the allocation of resources, to ensure the business environment and to make the market more open, the statement says.
The government will also release controls on the powers it delegates to firms and make sure that the firms themselves decide how to run their business.
The statement also states that China will allow the border areas to discover new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to promote regional growth.
In an effort to open up the state-controlled sector, more areas will be open to private investment.
"The government will not change its policy towards foreign investment and will protect the legal interests of companies that are financed from abroad and will provide them with better services," the statement reads.
In addition, it will be easier for foreigners to apply for a permanent residence permit or for a "green card," by optimizing the requirements and simplifying the application process.
Providing the rights of attorneys to practise and develop professional judges and the prosecutor was also discussed at the meeting.
The meeting was also attended by Prime Minister Li Keqiang and Lecturers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli, according to a statement issued after the meeting.
