According to the Deputy Governor of the Karlovy Vary Region, Jakub Pánik (ČSSD), the current capacity of the inpatient wards of two regional hospitals and two private hospitals in the region is sufficient and partial modifications should be made on the basis of an agreement between departments of individual hospitals.
In the region, however, there are also possibilities of expanding care.
